INSERT INTO `guestbook` VALUES (1,'2006-06-23','Vaz Roger','Curitiba','Brazil','rvaz@unicenp.edu.br','Hello Mr. Vaz, here is another relative ... from Brazil.. congratulations for your outstanding work.\n\nRoger Vaz,BMD,PhD\nCuritiba,Parana Brazil'),(2,'2006-05-18','Heiko H.','Berlin','Germany','http://www.trekkingforum.com/forum/showthread.php?t=5344','Hallo,\n\nIch habe bei http://video.google.com eine Video über Sikkim gefunden.. http://video.google.com/videoplay?do...77198 q=sikkim über 30 Minuten mit Landschaftsbildern, dem Toytrain, Tempelfesten usw..\n\nsehr empfehlenswert.\nsiehe auch\nhttp://www.davaz.com/gallery/artwork...ND1999-AAC0001'),(3,'2006-05-18','Flo F.','Berlin','Germany','Trekkingforum.com','Google Video: Sikkim Stories - Trekkingforum.com - 12. Mai\nVon diesem Jürg da Vaz gibts bei google ein weiteres knapp dreiviertel-stündiges Video über Bhutan, ebenfalls in diesem beobachtenden Stil gehalten: ...\nFlo'),(4,'2006-05-12','Katsunori Takahashi','Kanazawa','Japan',' otakacha@dc4.so-net.ne.jp','\nDate: 12. Mai 2006 14:50:10 GMT+02:00\nTo: juerg@davaz.com\n\nHi! \nDa Vaz-san,\nThank you for coming to Kanazawa. \nDo you arrive at Tokyo?\n\nTakahashi-san'),(5,'2006-05-11','Shun S.','Kanazawa','Japan','shun@unitize3.com','Mr. Da Vaz\n\nThanks for today\'s lecture. It was so exciting and amazing!\nAnd I\'m so happy that you gave me your work with an autograph :-)\n\nAfter the lecture, me and Yuta went back to the school and talked to classmates how interesting it was! All classmates said \"oh, we should have gone too...\"\n\nOn my way to home, I hit on a question for you. that is...\n\n\"What do you think about simple design/art?\"\n\nSome people say \"simple is boring.\", and other people say \"simple is good.\"\nI thought simple is good because it is easy to understand and I always create simple things. But today something happened to me at the 2D design class -unconscious drawing lesson- I draw very rough and random sketch that I ever drew. it was really fun! I was very surprised \"oh! I can draw like this!\"\nAfter that I\'m asking myself about \"what is simple design? is it good or not?\".\nI appreciate if you don\'t mind to answer my question.\n\nI hope you enjoy the rest of your staying in Japan.\n\nshun (a guy with yuta.)'),(6,'2006-05-11','Kojiro Satomi','Kanazawa','Japan','satomi@city.kanazawa.ishikawa.jp','From: 	  satomi@city.kanazawa.ishikawa.jp\nHoi! hoi! Hoi!\nDatum: 	10. Mai 2006 21:00 \n\nTo Mr.Juerg Da Vaz\nYour long-term stay at the invitation of Kanazawa City in Kanazawa comes to an end. Thank you.\nWhile you stay, there was able to take place various things:\n\nOutdoor baths(Onsen you like so much).\nBarbecued chicken(yakitori you eat so much).\nSo many Sushi(all the time, because Kanazwa has best fish).\n4 seminars etc.\nAnd your design.\nMeeting with many artists, art colleges, studios and factories every day.\nI have studied and learned very much from your activities.\nAnd I was very happy.\nYour gentleness was nice, too.\n\nI wish a day comes to meet you again.\n \nSatomi-san.\n'),(7,'2006-05-11','g. christian','münchen','deutschland','ganschinietz@yahoo.de','durch Zufall bin ich über ihren Film \"Itzhak Frey and Sohn\" bei google gestolpert. Sehr rührend!'),(8,'2006-04-27','Yuta K.','Kanazawa','Japan','tmsmy0914@yahoo.co.jp','  	 I am student in Kanazawa, Japan\nDatum: 27. April 2006\n\nDo you remember me?\n\nI met you yesterday(4/26)in Kanazawa at your Seminar CONCEPTS OF CREATIVE PROCESS at the City Business Center.\n\nAnd you gave me a DVD (Alice in wonderland). I want to go to see more of your films and works, but today I can\'t go to your Seminar at the Kanazawa Art University. I have class.\nI saw your DVD (Alice in wonderland) with my classmates. They said, that\'s interesting and they want to meet you.\n\nI was so glad to see you.\nI love your works,thank you.\n\nYuta'),(9,'2006-04-14','Colene Belli','Alma Ata','Kazakhstan','colbelli@hotmail.com','Hello,\nI wanted to take a moment and thank you so very much for your wonderful production video called \"Born to Move\".  I have thoroughly enjoyed it and wish to share it with friends and family.  I hesitate to do so without your permission, despite the ability to share the file on google so easily.\n\nI am affiliated with a Kazakhstan adoption agency and feel that your work will help many MANY children see first hand where they have come from, what their life and people are like in the years they were born.  You have really given us all a very special gift.  I would very much like to link our adoption agency site to your work and presently have your film clip available for our parents to view.\n\nWould you kindly allow me to copy your media onto a DVD and give it out this way as well?  Would you require any form of royalty or payment?   I would also like to direct parents to make contributions toward your work if this is acceptable.\n\nPlease let me know, and again, thank you!!\n\nColene '),(10,'2006-04-05','Ben neweurasia.net','Alma Ata','Kazakhstan','http://kazakhstan.neweurasia','An artists view\nby Ben, posted on Sunday, February 19th, 2006 at 7:10 pm\n\nThrough Google Video, you can access one of Swiss artist Da Vazs videos on Kazakhstan. This, well, unorthodox artist has been travelling through Kazakhstan and produced a 1.5-hour documentary without annoying commentary.\n\nIt contains very interesting perspectives from throughout the country - some bleak, some rather funny - and is recommended viewing for all those who have a boring assignment to do and can afford to have a Google Video window open on the edge of the screen. The choice of music throughout the film ranges from traditional Kazakh music via Abba (!) to full-blown club tunes (some of which is rather misfortunate).\n\nOf note are the shots from the dry Aral Sea bed, the Russian exodus and the impressions from Astana at the end of the film. Da Vaz allocated a lot of his film time driving around in a car, in my opinion catching the endless width of the Kazakh steppe quite well. However, by spending such long time along the main roads, the images are also quite misrepresentative as their overall feel is rather desolate and Kazakhstan certainly has many very beautiful spots as well. And while loads of cars break down on Kazakh roads, Da Vaz must have an obsession with burst tyres and other misfortunes on Central Asian roads.\n\nIf you wonder how Da Vaz works, check out this TV-feature on his stint at a Kazakh media school. His filming techniques are certainly quite unique, not only for the Kazakh students. Maybe because, in Da Vazs words:\n\n    He refused to go to any Art college. He disliked the idea of learning the basic techniques. The outcome? A movement called, Da Vaz.\n    For Da Vaz, its not a question of techniques but how one evolves that along with the creative process. When you go through his work, he urges you not to search for his intentions behind them. Its how you perceive them thats important. \n\nAlso check out this short preview of his documentary on the Aral Sea. '),(11,'2006-03-30','Tatyana Khalzova','Kostanay','Kazakhstan','tanyaalau@list.ru','Hi Jürg,\nHow do you do?\nI stayed at grandmother Masha recently. There were relatives, we all look at BABUSHKA MASHA film.\nThey looked and smiled.\nThey liked the film.\n\nI think the film is a document about history. \n\nBabushka Masha says hello and invites you to visit her.\nTatyana'),(12,'2006-03-28','Wolfgang Mertin','Berlin','Deutschland','mertinfassbier@web.de','Hallo lieber Jürg,\nhabe mir Deinen Kamtschatka-Film angeschaut. Sehr gut die Geschichte rund um die Fischer, sehr emotional  mit den Zeichnungen am Schluß vertieft.\nAußerordentlich gut die Musik.\nWolfgang'),(14,'2006-03-10','Yousif Hamdona','Gaza','Palestine','y_hamdona@hotmail.com','Hi Juerg,\nIn fact HUMUS for HAMAS indicates the lives of Palestinian people, who live under occupation and seige. Your film reflects the real life of the Palestinians.\nMy regards\nY. Hamdona, Gaza'),(15,'2006-03-09','Zeno Davatz','Zurich','Switzerland','zdavatz@ywesee.com','Hallo Jürg\nDeine Filme sind reiner Rock\'n Roll. \nMit Gruss\nZeno'),(16,'2006-01-26','Brattain Mark','Hobart, IN','USA','izakar@aol.com','Hello. I found this site with a Google search. My great grandfather was Johannes Davatz, who was born in Graubunden and moved to Indianapolis. His daughter, Anna Davatz Otto (1903-1988), was my grandmother. '),(17,'2005-02-16','james Dee','london','uk','3lilgees@london.com','Hi,\nWe invite you to visit us for music, fashion, skateboarding and entertainment. We are 3Gees Entertainment Promotions and we can be found @  http://www.3gees.co.uk  .'),(18,'2004-08-14','Peterffy Iya','Krasnoyarsk','Russia','etn2002@mail.ru','Dear sir! Helloy!  Excuse for my bad English. I want to find the Hungarian relatives whom never saw. My name Peterffy Ija Andreevna, I live in Russia to Krasnoyarsk (Siberia). \nMy father  Peterffy  Andrey Albertovich  (András) was the officer formed by the person, in Krasnoyarsk worked as the teacher. In 1938 was has been executed  in Krasnoyarsk prison. Was born 11.02.1892 on farm Las Lotanen or Los-Lotanosn, Hungary. Brother Albert, sisters Irma and Erzhi, lived in Hungary, brother Alexander lived in Romania, Buzam-Besh.\nI have no other data on the Hungarian related communications. If you concern my family write to me.\netn2002@mail.ru\n'),(19,'2004-06-26','NWA ABA','LAG','USA','aba@yahoo.fr','I VISITE YOUR GOOD SITE.'),(20,'2004-04-09','Wackman Tom','Washington, D.C.','USA','Tom Wackman','great website!\n\nTom'),(21,'2004-03-31','asaba owerri','aba','Lagos','homeboy_owerri_asaba@aba.us','I love this page. It looks really nice. Keep it up.'),(22,'2004-01-15','beck eugen','lugano','switzerland','eugenbeck@hotmail.com','schweigen ist gold, silber...? eugen'),(23,'2003-11-16','Ran DeBord','Houston','USA','randebordart@houston.rr.com','I too, am an Artist, and very much enjoyed your art as well as very much appreciate your web site design\nMany thanks\nRan DeBord'),(24,'2003-11-15','Talgat Dairbakov','Alma Ata','Kazakhstan','talgat@eamedia.org','You have a very interesting website.\n\nLooking forward to see you somewhere in the World.\n\nSincerely yours\nTalgat\n'),(25,'2003-10-02','zo oezo','togo','lome','mug@mug.com','i like this  iteeeeeeeeeeeeeee'),(26,'2003-08-07','ansah samuel quansah','accra','ghana','elvisqua@yahoo.com','hi mr da vaz,\nthank you for your art work round the world and i think you are one of the great artist i have see.\nplease will lke to no more about you.\ni am also an artist from ghana,and i am 23 years of age,i will be very if you can accept me as your friend.\ni have send you e-mail.\nbye\nmy e-mail is;elvisqua@yahoo.com'),(27,'2003-08-01','Eleftheriou George','Athens','Greece','xzographos@hotmail.com','Hi George. We have seen me and my family, your homepage and was excited!!!Your work is so perfect and unusual. Congratulations....\nWith love, George\'s family from Hermioni.'),(28,'2003-06-05','Grishina nadia(fresh man)','moscow','Russia','laserda@mail.ru','Hello!\nI miss miss miss miss miss miss miss miss miss you! Where are you? I am so glad that I visit your site. Why are you don\'t write me  letters.\nYour pictures are very beautiful!\nThank you!!!!!!'),(29,'2003-05-08','Britvina Julija','Moscow','Russia','kitten-julie@yandex.ru','Hallo, Herr Ürg! Actually we\'ve never met before. So I visited your home page by chance. May be you remember the incedent in the train in Russia, where you got to know a woman-conductor Olga. But I wasnt going to speak about that. I\'m sort of an artist too, but more amateur now than a professional. I was really impressed by the paintings on your web-page and the web-page itself is an artwork. It\'s so wonderful, I can\'t even find the right words to express everything I feel. Hope to see you one day and talk about your work. Thank you.'),(30,'2003-02-01','Paulella Marilene','São Paulo','Brasil','rubensjp@netpoint.com.br','Cher Monsieur Da Vaz\n\nJ\'avais jamais entendu parler\nde votre nom! C\'est dommage!\nQuelle belle page ! Je cherchais\ndes informations sur la Colonie\nIbicaba du Senateur Vergueiro (Thomas Davatz)\net j\'ai tombée amoureuse de\nvotre beau travail!\nMes compliments\nMarilene Siqueira Paulella'),(31,'2002-12-03','Joy Rose','London','UK','JR1997@hotmail.com','Hello!\nHow old are you?\nMarvelous works!\nJoy'),(32,'2002-09-17','Kublai Dai','Norfolk','USA','kublaidai@hotmail.com','Hello! Dear Da Vaz:\nHow are you?\nRecently I\'m teaching art class in the States and I suggested my American students to search your webpage because I think you are a very important contemporary artist they should know.Mybe they will write something for you later.\nBest wishes!\nProf. Dai Yu from USA\n'),(34,'2001-11-22','Takeshi Matsuda','Tokyo','Japan','tmatsuda23@hotmail.com','Dear Mr. Da Vaz,\n\nMy mane is Takeshi Matsuda, a graduate student who met you at NHK in Tokyo.\nI reached your Homepage and really enjoyed it. I was surprised to find the web-site itself was an attractive production! \nAlthough I felt your sense of filming was unique, I must confess that I didn\'t\nknow you were such an active and great artist at that time. As my mother is a painter, I\'ve been very much interested in artistic expression.\nI would like to talk with you more next time.\n\nBest regards\nTakeshi Matsuda'),(35,'2001-11-20','Proctor Eric','Canmore','Canada','proctor@btvf.com','Hello from the Rockie Mountains of Canada!\n\nIt was so good to meet you at the Japan Prize - many fond memories.\n\nThought I\'d surf your web site - you\nare definitely one strange bird - perhaps an Eagle with Silver Wings.\n\nI hope to send you a copy of the photo from the temple.\n\nHope all your cabbages are keeping well\n\n\ncheers my friend'),(36,'2001-07-07','Tsilivigos Elias','Ermioni','Greece','mr_spock_99@hotmail.com','I am sorry to say I never knew Da Vaz has been in my little town, so, you can imagine how amazed I am! The work is a true miracle, but who am I to comment on your work anyway! I\'d really like to see you back here some time, and we can even organize an honorary art exhibition here. Thank you, take care.\n\nGreetings from Greece\n\nLiakos'),(37,'2001-07-03','Lilian Wu','Shanghai','China','lilianwu@elong.com','Hi Juerg,\nBy the way, I visited your website. It is a wonderful website and I like it. The structure is very clear and the page is mostly eyes catching. Did you designed it yourself?  \nGood luck!!\n \nLilian\n'),(38,'2001-07-03','William Jin','Hangzhou','China','zdjxw@mail.hz.zj.cn','\nDear Da Vaz:\n\nYour web background picture makes profound effect on me. I like it. It is like China GuanSu DunHuan fresco. If you have time, you must travel there. Maybe it can give you some inspiration.\nHope I can meet you again in China. \nGood luck. Keep touch.\n\nWilliam Jin\n\n         '),(39,'2001-05-06','Shi Qi','Hangzhou','China','zhouyan99@21cn.com','Hello,   \nI\'m Shi Qi, your student of China National Academy of Fine Arts. Do you rerember ?  Are you ok ? when are you coming to china again ?  Now our school has being moving to Xiao Shan because of reconstruction.We all want to see you again \nbey-bey \nShi Qi'),(40,'2001-05-06','Rooma Shyam','New Delhi','India','indira@bharat.net','Hello\nI love your site. please let me know who desigend it.\nregards\nRooma\n'),(41,'2001-05-06','Mao Imaizumi','Tokyo','Japan','t97107mi@sfc.keio.ac.jp','Dear Juerg Da Vaz\nI saw your web-site and enjoyed it so much.\nI like the part of \"His Inspiration\" and your drawing \"when the man loves woman\" and the drawing of the top-page.\nYours sincerely,\nMao Imaizumi'),(42,'2001-05-06','Ruth Mühle','Solothurn','Switzerland','r.gauch@bluewin.ch','Lieber Jürg,  \nIch bin in Deinen Internetauftritt gesurft, eine wahre Performence. Es ist die anmachenste (!) und schönste und spannenste webside, welche ich bisher besucht habe. Der Auftritt ist echt gut. \nGruss Ruth'),(43,'2001-05-06','Linda Davaz','Lake Forest','California USA','lindaattuttles@yahoo.com','Dear Juerg, I\'m sitting here looking at your web site with my father and mother, Allen and Eula Davaz. We want to say hello to you. We love your art work. \nLinda Davaz in California '),(44,'2001-05-06','Susanne and Magnus Andersson','Zürich','Switzerland','andersson@swissonline.ch','Hi Jürg,\nI was having a look at your homepage. It looks really nice. It was\ninteresting to read about your family history and that you have traced it so\nfar back.\nKind Regards\nMagnus '),(51,'2007-04-21','Belmiro Freitas','Criciúma, Santa Catarina','Brazil','jb6060@gmail.com','Good evening. \nMy name is João Belmiro Freitas, I live in Criciúma, Santa Catarina - Brazil.\nI had chance to attend the excellent set of documents \"Old Ponds\" and found the music of deep fascinating of the documentary related one.\nAlready I tried to search for the Internet some times and I do not obtain to discover the name and the author of this gorgeous music.\nWould it be possible to answer this email saying which is the name and the author of the music subject of this set of documents?\nBeing thankful and congratulating vocês for the excellent work.\n\nGreetings.\nBelmiro, Criciúma, Santa Catarina - Brazil'),(52,'2007-09-08','Sidler Cornelia','Basle','Switzerland','cornelia.sidler@ukbb.ch','Hello Urle und Juerg\r\nHabe an Euch gedacht, als ich gestern ueber die Karlsbruecke in Prag promeniert bin. Die Gruppe Jazz no problem hatte dort einen Auftritt und wenn ich mich recht erinnere, hatten sie bei Eurem Fest in Prag gespielt....\r\nHerzliche Gruesse aus Prag + hope to seeyou again.\r\nNele'),(53,'2008-02-09','Pieter van Diest pieter','Hasselt','Belgium','pvandiest@live.com','found you through google and must say your movies are great!\n\nPieter\n\nwww.champagnevoordeel.be'),(54,'2008-07-20','bob jan','alkmaar','holland','bobjansenart@tiscali.nl','nice things\r\n\r\n\r\nhttp://www.bodato.com\r\nhttp://www.bobjansen-art.nl'),(82,'2010-11-15','lorenz davatz ','','','','hello, I was wondering about any Davatz,that came from switzerland. Where do they live in Brazil, and Anna Davatz'),(79,'2010-02-02','Burak ','','','','Yor!\nI got \"FURNITURE in AFGHANISTAN\", I got my name in titles, but I did\'nt got any women on film!!  Life out of time.\nThank you for your job.\nRespect and hug\nYur'),(81,'2010-02-03','Brueschweiler ','','','','Lieber Jürg\n<br />Ich bin ein kleiner Kunstsammler geworden und habe Künstler-Freunde in Köln, unter anderem Michael Toenges.\n<br />Er hat mir letzthin geschrieben, dass er (ein ausgebildeter wunderbarer und kunsthistorisch gescheiter Kunstmaler) <b>Sehnsucht hat nach dem &quot;Anfängerglück&quot;, dass im Mangel an Können und Vollkommenheit ein substanzieller Bestandteil liege der Malerei, dass der Mangel eine Offenheit im Bild erzeugen kann</b> usw. \n<br />Da habe ich mich an den Artikel von Ursula erinnert &quot;Kunst und Evolution&quot; und habe dabei auch an deine Arbeiten gedacht. Ich sehe da eine geistige Verwandtschaft in der Auffassung ueber die Kunst, obwohl eure Arbeiten (Gott sei dank) unterschiedlicher nicht sein könnten. So gab das eine das andere und deshalb bin ich &quot;bei dir gelandet&quot;.\n<br />Matthias'),(74,'2010-01-06','bollywo','New Dehli','India','bollywo@gmail.com','INDIA / The OTHER EYE - 29:33\nWhich unforgettable epics, songs and stories are created! Filmed on site in Bollywood, Bombay, India a handmade Da Vaz production. \nbollywo.com');
